# --- HUNK 1: Lines 1-68 ---
     1| <?php
     2| namespace JSONStream;
     3| class CollectionReader {
     4|     protected const CHUNK_SIZE = 8192;
     5|     protected $resource;
     6|     protected bool $asArray = false;
     7|     protected string $buffer = '';
     8|     protected int $nestingLevel = 0;
     9|     public function __construct(string $path, bool $asArray = true) {
    10|         if (!file_exists($path)) {
    11|             throw new \InvalidArgumentException('There is no file at given path');
    12|         }
    13|         $this->asArray = $asArray;
    14|         $this->resource = fopen($path, 'rb');
    15|     }
    16|     public function close(): void {
    17|         if (is_resource($this->resource)) {
    18|             fclose($this->resource);
    19|         }
    20|     }
    21|     public function get(): \Generator {
    22|         $this->buffer = '';
    23|         $this->nestingLevel = 0;
    24|         rewind($this->resource);
    25|         while (!feof($this->resource)) {
    26|             $chunk = fread($this->resource, self::CHUNK_SIZE);
    27|             yield from $this->parseChunk($chunk);
    28|         }
    29|     }
    30|     private function parseChunk($chunk): \Generator {
    31|         $this->buffer .= $chunk;
    32|         $start = 0;
    33|         $keepFrom = 0;
    34|         $yielded = 0;
    35|         $split = mb_str_split($this->buffer);
    36|         foreach ($split as $position => $char) {
    37|             if ($this->nestingLevel === 0 && $char === '[') {
    38|                 continue;
    39|             }
    40|             if ($this->nestingLevel === 0 && $char === ']') {
    41|                 break;
    42|             }
    43|             if ($char === '{') {
    44|                 if ($this->nestingLevel === 0) {
    45|                     $start = $position;
    46|                 }
    47|                 $this->nestingLevel++;
    48|             } elseif ($char === '}') {
    49|                 $this->nestingLevel--;
    50|                 if ($this->nestingLevel === 0) {
    51|                     $keepFrom = $position + 1;
    52|                     yield json_decode(
    53|                         mb_substr($this->buffer, $start, $position - $start + 1),
    54|                         $this->asArray
    55|                     );
    56|                     $yielded++;
    57|                 }
    58|             }
    59|         }
    60|         if ($yielded === 0) {
    61|             $this->nestingLevel = 0;
    62|         }
    63|         $this->buffer = mb_substr($this->buffer, $keepFrom);
    64|     }
    65|     public function __destruct() {
    66|         $this->close();
    67|     }
    68| }

     1| <?php
     2| namespace JSONStream;
     3| class CollectionWriter {
     4|     protected $resource;
     5|     protected int $key = 0;
     6|     public function __construct(string $path) {
     7|         file_put_contents($path, '');
     8|         $this->resource = fopen($path, 'wb');
     9|         fwrite($this->resource, '[');
    10|     }
    11|     public function push($item): void {
    12|         if ($this->key !== 0) {
    13|             fwrite($this->resource, ',');
    14|         }
    15|         fwrite($this->resource, json_encode($item));
    16|         $this->key++;
    17|     }
    18|     public function close(): void {
    19|         if (is_resource($this->resource)) {
    20|             fwrite($this->resource, ']');
    21|             fclose($this->resource);
    22|         }
    23|     }
    24|     public function __destruct() {
    25|         $this->close();
    26|     }
    27| }

    80|     private function parseEvent(array $event)
    81|     {
    82|         if (!empty($event['headers'][':message-type'])) {
    83|             if ($event['headers'][':message-type'] === 'error') {
    84|                 return $this->parseError($event);
    85|             }
    86|             if ($event['headers'][':message-type'] === 'exception') {
    87|                 return $this->parseException($event);
    88|             }
    89|             if ($event['headers'][':message-type'] !== 'event') {
    90|                 throw new ParserException('Failed to parse unknown message type.');
    91|             }
    92|         }
    93|         $eventType = $event['headers'][':event-type'] ?? null;
    94|         if (empty($eventType)) {
    95|             throw new ParserException('Failed to parse without event type.');
    96|         }
    97|         $eventPayload = $event['payload'];
    98|         if ($eventType === 'initial-response') {
    99|             return $this->parseInitialResponseEvent($eventPayload);
   100|         }
   101|         $eventShape = $this->shape->getMember($eventType);
   102|         return [

   104|                 $this->parseEventHeaders($event['headers'], $eventShape),
   105|                 $this->parseEventPayload($eventPayload, $eventShape)
   106|             )
   107|         ];
   108|     }

    37|         ?callable $bytesGenerator = null

    39|         return function (callable $handler) use ($service, $bytesGenerator) {
    40|             return new self($handler, $service, $bytesGenerator);
    41|         };
    42|     }

    44|     public function __invoke(CommandInterface $cmd) {

     7|  * A custom mutator for a GetBucketLocation request, which
     8|  * extract the bucket location value and injects it into the
     9|  * result as the `LocationConstraint` field.
    10|  *
    11|  * @internal
    12|  */
    13| final class GetBucketLocationResultMutator implements S3ResultMutator
    14| {
    15|     /**
    16|      * @inheritDoc
    17|      */
    18|     public function __invoke(
    19|         ResultInterface $result,
    20|         CommandInterface $command,
    21|         ResponseInterface $response
    22|     ): ResultInterface
    23|     {
    24|         if ($command->getName() !== 'GetBucketLocation') {
    25|             return $result;
    26|         }
    27|         $location = 'us-east-1';
    28|         static $pattern = '/>(.+?)<\/LocationConstraint>/';
    29|         if (preg_match($pattern, $response->getBody(), $matches)) {
    30|             $location = $matches[1] === 'EU' ? 'eu-west-1' : $matches[1];
    31|         }
    32|         $result['LocationConstraint'] = $location;
    33|         $response->getBody()->rewind();
    34|         return $result;
    35|     }
    36| }

   265|     protected function ensureDirectoryExists(string $dirname, int $visibility): void
   266|     {

   269|         }

   278|         }
   279|     }

    38|     {
    39|         $this->id = $id;
    40|         $this->text = $text;
    41|         $this->line = $line;
    42|         $this->pos = $position;
    43|     }
    44|     public function getTokenName(): ?string
    45|     {
    46|         if ('UNKNOWN' === $name = token_name($this->id)) {
    47|             $name = \strlen($this->text) > 1 || \ord($this->text) < 32 ? null : $this->text;
    48|         }
    49|         return $name;
    50|     }
    51|     /**
    52|      * @param int|string|array $kind
    53|      */
    54|     public function is($kind): bool
    55|     {
    56|         foreach ((array) $kind as $value) {
    57|             if (\in_array($value, [$this->id, $this->text], true)) {
    58|                 return true;
    59|             }
    60|         }
    61|         return false;
    62|     }
    63|     public function isIgnorable(): bool
    64|     {
    65|         return \in_array($this->id, [\T_WHITESPACE, \T_COMMENT, \T_DOC_COMMENT, \T_OPEN_TAG], true);
    66|     }
    67|     public function __toString(): string
    68|     {
    69|         return (string) $this->text;
    70|     }
    71|     /**
    72|      * @return list<static>
    73|      */
    74|     public static function tokenize(string $code, int $flags = 0): array
    75|     {
    76|         $line = 1;
    77|         $position = 0;
    78|         $tokens = token_get_all($code, $flags);
    79|         foreach ($tokens as $index => $token) {
    80|             if (\is_string($token)) {
    81|                 $id = \ord($token);
    82|                 $text = $token;
    83|             } else {
    84|                 [$id, $text, $line] = $token;
    85|             }
    86|             $tokens[$index] = new static($id, $text, $line, $position);
    87|             $position += \strlen($text);
    88|         }
    89|         return $tokens;
    90|     }

    11| use Psr\Container\ContainerExceptionInterface;
    12| use Psr\Container\NotFoundExceptionInterface;
    13| class_exists(ContainerExceptionInterface::class);
    14| class_exists(NotFoundExceptionInterface::class);
    15| /**
    16|  * A trait to help implement ServiceProviderInterface.
    17|  *
    18|  * @author Robin Chalas <robin.chalas@gmail.com>
    19|  * @author Nicolas Grekas <p@tchwork.com>
    20|  */
    21| trait ServiceLocatorTrait
    22| {
    23|     private array $loading = [];
    24|     private array $providedTypes;
    25|     /**
    26|      * @param array<string, callable> $factories
    27|      */
    28|     public function __construct(
    29|         private array $factories,
    30|     ) {
    31|     }
    32|     public function has(string $id): bool
    33|     {
    34|         return isset($this->factories[$id]);
    35|     }
    36|     public function get(string $id): mixed
    37|     {
    38|         if (!isset($this->factories[$id])) {
    39|             throw $this->createNotFoundException($id);
    40|         }
    41|         if (isset($this->loading[$id])) {
    42|             $ids = array_values($this->loading);
    43|             $ids = \array_slice($this->loading, array_search($id, $ids));
    44|             $ids[] = $id;
    45|             throw $this->createCircularReferenceException($id, $ids);
    46|         }
    47|         $this->loading[$id] = $id;
    48|         try {
    49|             return $this->factories[$id]($this);
    50|         } finally {

# --- HUNK 2: Lines 56-94 ---
    56|         if (!isset($this->providedTypes)) {
    57|             $this->providedTypes = [];
    58|             foreach ($this->factories as $name => $factory) {
    59|                 if (!\is_callable($factory)) {
    60|                     $this->providedTypes[$name] = '?';
    61|                 } else {
    62|                     $type = (new \ReflectionFunction($factory))->getReturnType();
    63|                     $this->providedTypes[$name] = $type ? ($type->allowsNull() ? '?' : '').($type instanceof \ReflectionNamedType ? $type->getName() : $type) : '?';
    64|                 }
    65|             }
    66|         }
    67|         return $this->providedTypes;
    68|     }
    69|     private function createNotFoundException(string $id): NotFoundExceptionInterface
    70|     {
    71|         if (!$alternatives = array_keys($this->factories)) {
    72|             $message = 'is empty...';
    73|         } else {
    74|             $last = array_pop($alternatives);
    75|             if ($alternatives) {
    76|                 $message = \sprintf('only knows about the "%s" and "%s" services.', implode('", "', $alternatives), $last);
    77|             } else {
    78|                 $message = \sprintf('only knows about the "%s" service.', $last);
    79|             }
    80|         }
    81|         if ($this->loading) {
    82|             $message = \sprintf('The service "%s" has a dependency on a non-existent service "%s". This locator %s', end($this->loading), $id, $message);
    83|         } else {
    84|             $message = \sprintf('Service "%s" not found: the current service locator %s', $id, $message);
    85|         }
    86|         return new class($message) extends \InvalidArgumentException implements NotFoundExceptionInterface {
    87|         };
    88|     }
    89|     private function createCircularReferenceException(string $id, array $path): ContainerExceptionInterface
    90|     {
    91|         return new class(\sprintf('Circular reference detected for service "%s", path: "%s".', $id, implode(' -> ', $path))) extends \RuntimeException implements ContainerExceptionInterface {
    92|         };
    93|     }
    94| }

# --- HUNK 1: Lines 17-64 ---
    17|  *
    18|  * Service ids are available as "ClassName::methodName" so that the implementation
    19|  * of subscriber methods can be just `return $this->container->get(__METHOD__);`.
    20|  *
    21|  * @author Kevin Bond <kevinbond@gmail.com>
    22|  */
    23| trait ServiceMethodsSubscriberTrait
    24| {
    25|     protected ContainerInterface $container;
    26|     public static function getSubscribedServices(): array
    27|     {
    28|         $services = method_exists(get_parent_class(self::class) ?: '', __FUNCTION__) ? parent::getSubscribedServices() : [];
    29|         foreach ((new \ReflectionClass(self::class))->getMethods() as $method) {
    30|             if (self::class !== $method->getDeclaringClass()->name) {
    31|                 continue;
    32|             }
    33|             if (!$attribute = $method->getAttributes(SubscribedService::class)[0] ?? null) {
    34|                 continue;
    35|             }
    36|             if ($method->isStatic() || $method->isAbstract() || $method->isGenerator() || $method->isInternal() || $method->getNumberOfRequiredParameters()) {
    37|                 throw new \LogicException(\sprintf('Cannot use "%s" on method "%s::%s()" (can only be used on non-static, non-abstract methods with no parameters).', SubscribedService::class, self::class, $method->name));
    38|             }
    39|             if (!$returnType = $method->getReturnType()) {
    40|                 throw new \LogicException(\sprintf('Cannot use "%s" on methods without a return type in "%s::%s()".', SubscribedService::class, $method->name, self::class));
    41|             }
    42|             /* @var SubscribedService $attribute */
    43|             $attribute = $attribute->newInstance();
    44|             $attribute->key ??= self::class.'::'.$method->name;
    45|             $attribute->type ??= $returnType instanceof \ReflectionNamedType ? $returnType->getName() : (string) $returnType;
    46|             $attribute->nullable = $attribute->nullable ?: $returnType->allowsNull();
    47|             if ($attribute->attributes) {
    48|                 $services[] = $attribute;
    49|             } else {
    50|                 $services[$attribute->key] = ($attribute->nullable ? '?' : '').$attribute->type;
    51|             }
    52|         }
    53|         return $services;
    54|     }
    55|     public function setContainer(ContainerInterface $container): ?ContainerInterface
    56|     {
    57|         $ret = null;
    58|         if (method_exists(get_parent_class(self::class) ?: '', __FUNCTION__)) {
    59|             $ret = parent::setContainer($container);
    60|         }
    61|         $this->container = $container;
    62|         return $ret;
    63|     }
    64| }

    28|     public function lockResourceId($resourceId, $user = null) {
    29|         if (!$resourceId) {
    30|             return false;
    31|         }
    32|         $key  = "locked:{$resourceId}";
    33|         $user = $user ?? $this->app->helper('auth')->getUser();
    34|         if (!$user) {
    35|             return false;
    36|         }
    37|         $now = time();

    39|             'rid'  => $resourceId,
    40|             'user' => ['_id' => $user['_id'], 'name' => $user['name'] ?? '', 'user' => $user['user'], 'email' => $user['email']],

    42|             'time' => $now,
    43|             '_created' => $now,
    44|             '_updated' => $now,
    45|         ];
    46|         $this->app->dataStorage->setKey('app/options', $key, $meta);
    47|         return true;
    48|     }
    49|     public function updateLockedResourceId($resourceId) {

    51|         if (!$this->isResourceEditableByCurrentUser($resourceId)) {

    21|     public function makeAssetLocalAvailable(string $path) {
    22|         $path = trim($path, '/');
    23|         $src = $this->app->path("#uploads:{$path}");
    24|         if (!$src && $this->app->fileStorage->fileExists("uploads://{$path}")) {
    25|             $stream = $this->app->fileStorage->readStream("uploads://{$path}");
    26|             if ($stream) {
    27|                 $this->app->fileStorage->writeStream("#uploads://{$path}", $stream);
    28|                 $src = $this->app->path("#uploads:{$path}");
    29|             }
    30|         }
    31|         return $src;
    32|     }
    33|     public function image(array $options = [], bool $asPath = false) {
    34|         $options = array_merge([
    35|             'storage' => $this->storage,
    36|             'src' => '',
    37|             'mode' => 'thumbnail',
    38|             'mime' => null,
    39|             'fp' => null,
    40|             'filters' => [],
    41|             'width' => false,
    42|             'height' => false,
    43|             'quality' => 100,
    44|             'rebuild' => false,
    45|             'base64' => false,
    46|             'timestamp' => null
    47|         ], $options);
    48|         extract($options);
    49|         if (!$width && !$height) {
    50|             return ['error' => 'Target width or height parameter is missing'];
    51|         }
    52|         if (!$src) {
    53|             return ['error' => 'Missing src parameter'];
    54|         }
    55|         $hash = $mime ? md5(json_encode($options))."_{$quality}_{$mode}.{$mime}" : null;
    56|         if (!$rebuild && $mime) {
    57|             $thumbpath = $storage."/{$hash}";
    58|             if ($this->app->fileStorage->fileExists($thumbpath)) {
    59|                 if ($base64) {
    60|                     return "data:image/{$mime};base64,".base64_encode($this->app->fileStorage->read($thumbpath));
    61|                 }
    62|                 return $asPath ? $thumbpath : $this->app->fileStorage->getURL($thumbpath);
    63|             }
    64|         }
    65|         $src = rawurldecode($src);
    66|         if (str_contains($src, '../')) {
    67|             $src = implode('/', array_filter(explode('/', $src), fn ($s) => trim($s, '.')));
    68|         }

    70|         if (str_starts_with($src, 'uploads://')) {
    71|             $options['src'] = str_replace('uploads://', '', $src);
    72|             return $this->imageByPath($options, $asPath, $hash);
    73|         }
    74|         return $this->imageByAsset($options, $asPath, $hash);
    75|     }
    76|     protected function imageByAsset(array $options = [], bool $asPath = false, ?string $hash = null) {
    77|         extract($options);
    78|         $asset = null;
    79|         if (str_starts_with($src, 'assets://')) {
    80|             $asset = ['path' => \str_replace('assets://', '', $src)];
    81|         } elseif (!preg_match('/\.(png|jpg|jpeg|gif|svg|webp)$/i', $src)) {
    82|             $asset = $this->app->dataStorage->findOne('assets', ['_id' => $src]);
    83|         } else {
    84|             $asset = $this->app->dataStorage->findOne('assets', ['path' => $src]);
    85|         }
    86|         if (!$asset) {
    87|             return ['error' => 'Asset not found'];
    88|         }
    89|         $options['src'] = $asset['path'];
    90|         if (!$fp && isset($asset['fp']['x'], $asset['fp']['y'])) {
    91|             $options['fp'] = "{$asset['fp']['x']} {$asset['fp']['y']}";
    92|         }
    93|         return $this->imageByPath($options, $asPath, $hash);
    94|     }
    95|     protected function imageByPath(array $options = [], bool $asPath = false, ?string $hash = null) {

   101|             return false;

   107|             }

   115|                 ]);

   117|                     return false;
   118|                 }
   119|             }

     1| <?php
     2| namespace Assets\Utils;
     3| use Symfony\Component\Process\Process;
     4| use Symfony\Component\Process\Exception\ProcessFailedException;
     5| class Ffmpeg {
     6|     protected string $binary = 'ffmpeg';
     7|     /**
     8|      * @param string|null $binary
     9|      */
    10|     public function __construct(?string $binary = null) {
    11|         if ($binary) {
    12|             $this->binary = $binary;
    13|         }
    14|     }
    15|     /**
    16|      * @param string $dest
    17|      * @param array $options
    18|      * @return void
    19|      */
    20|     public function thumbnail(string $dest, array $options = []) {
    21|         $options = array_merge([
    22|             'src' => null,
    23|             'scan' => 10
    24|         ], $options);
    25|         $options['scan'] = intval($options['scan']);
    26|         $command = "{$this->binary} -hwaccel auto -i '{$options['src']}' -vf 'thumbnail=n={$options['scan']}' -frames:v 1 '{$dest}'";
    27|         $process = Process::fromShellCommandline($command);
    28|         $process->setTimeout(25);
    29|         $process->run();
    30|     }
    31|     public function getVideoMeta(string $src): ?array {
    32|         $command = "{$this->binary} -i '{$src}' 2>&1";
    33|         $process = Process::fromShellCommandline($command);
    34|         $process->run();
    35|         $output = $process->getOutput();
    36|         $meta = [
    37|             'duration' => null,
    38|             'width' => null,
    39|             'height' => null,

# --- HUNK 2: Lines 41-153 ---
    41|         ];
    42|         if (preg_match('/Duration:\s*(\d+):(\d+):(\d+)(?:\.(\d+))?/', $output, $matches)) {
    43|             $hours = (int)$matches[1];
    44|             $minutes = (int)$matches[2];
    45|             $seconds = (int)$matches[3];
    46|             $milliseconds = isset($matches[4]) ? (float)("0." . $matches[4]) : 0;
    47|             $meta['duration'] = ($hours * 3600) + ($minutes * 60) + $seconds + $milliseconds;
    48|         }
    49|         if (preg_match('/Video:\s*([^(,\s]+)/', $output, $matches)) {
    50|             $meta['codec'] = trim($matches[1]);
    51|         }
    52|         if (preg_match('/,\s*(\d+)x(\d+)[\s,\[]/', $output, $matches)) {
    53|             $meta['width'] = (int)$matches[1];
    54|             $meta['height'] = (int)$matches[2];
    55|         }
    56|         if ($meta['duration'] === null && $meta['width'] === null) {
    57|             return null;
    58|         }
    59|         return $meta;
    60|     }
    61|     /**
    62|      * Transcodes a video based on the provided configuration.
    63|      *
    64|      * @param string $srcPath Path to the source video file.
    65|      * @param string $destPath Path to the destination video file.
    66|      * @param array $config Transcoding configuration options.
    67|      * Example: [
    68|      * 'video_codec' => 'libx264',       // e.g., -c:v libx264
    69|      * 'audio_codec' => 'aac',           // e.g., -c:a aac
    70|      * 'video_bitrate' => '1M',          // e.g., -b:v 1M
    71|      * 'audio_bitrate' => '128k',        // e.g., -b:a 128k
    72|      * 'resolution' => '1280x720',       // e.g., -s 1280x720 (for direct size setting)
    73|      * 'scale' => '1280:-2',             // e.g., -vf scale=1280:-2 (more flexible scaling, overrides 'resolution')
    74|      * 'preset' => 'medium',             // e.g., -preset medium (for x264/x265)
    75|      * 'crf' => 23,                      // e.g., -crf 23 (for x264/x265)
    76|      * 'framerate' => 30,                // e.g., -r 30
    77|      * 'format' => 'mp4',                // e.g., -f mp4 (output container format)
    78|      * 'pixel_format' => 'yuv420p',      // e.g., -pix_fmt yuv420p (for compatibility)
    79|      * 'audio_channels' => 2,            // e.g., -ac 2
    80|      * 'hwaccel' => 'auto',              // e.g., -hwaccel auto (set to null or false to disable)
    81|      * 'overwrite' => true,              // e.g., -y (overwrite output file if it exists)
    82|      * 'raw' => '',                      // e.g., '-movflags +faststart -profile:v main' (additional raw ffmpeg flags)
    83|      * 'timeout' => 3600,                // Process timeout in seconds (default: 1 hour)
    84|      * ]
    85|      * @return void
    86|      * @throws \InvalidArgumentException If source file is not found or not readable.
    87|      * @throws ProcessFailedException If the FFMPEG command fails (e.g., non-zero exit code).
    88|      */
    89|     public function transcode(string $srcPath, string $destPath, array $config = []): void {
    90|         if (!is_file($srcPath) || !is_readable($srcPath)) {
    91|             throw new \InvalidArgumentException("Source file not found or not readable: " . $srcPath);
    92|         }
    93|         $defaultConfig = [
    94|             'overwrite' => true,          // Overwrite output file if it exists
    95|             'timeout' => 3600,            // Default timeout: 1 hour
    96|             'hwaccel' => 'auto',          // Hardware acceleration ('auto', 'cuda', 'vaapi', etc., or null/false to disable)
    97|             'video_codec' => null,        // e.g., 'libx264', 'libvpx-vp9'
    98|             'audio_codec' => null,        // e.g., 'aac', 'libopus'
    99|             'video_bitrate' => null,      // e.g., '1M', '2500k'
   100|             'audio_bitrate' => null,      // e.g., '128k', '192k'
   101|             'resolution' => null,         // For -s WxH (e.g., '1280x720')

    23|     public function exec() {
    24|         $this->hasValidCsrfToken(true);
    25|         $command = trim($this->param('command', ''));
    26|         if (!$command) {

    30|             $command = substr($command, 6);

    32|         $command = "tower {$command}";
    33|         $phpBinaryPath = (new PhpExecutableFinder())->find();
    34|         $process = Process::fromShellCommandline("$phpBinaryPath {$command} -n");
